{
    "chapter": 87,
    "verses": {
        "1": {
            "verses": {
                "87:1": {
                    "id": 1
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>Glorify the Name of your Lord, that is, exalt your Lord above what does not befit Him (ism [in isma rabbika, `the Name of your Lord'] is extra), the Most High (an adjective qualifying rabbika, `your Lord'),</p>"
        },
        "2": {
            "verses": {
                "87:2": {
                    "id": 2
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>Who created and proportioned, His creature, making it of well-proportioned parts, without irregularities,</p>"
        },
        "3": {
            "verses": {
                "87:3": {
                    "id": 3
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and Who determined, what He wants, and guided, to what He had determined of good or evil,</p>"
        },
        "4": {
            "verses": {
                "87:4": {
                    "id": 4
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and Who brought forth the pasture, [Who] caused herbage to grow,</p>"
        },
        "5": {
            "verses": {
                "87:5": {
                    "id": 5
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>then made it, after verdancy, blackened stubble, desiccated broken chaff.</p>"
        },
        "6": {
            "verses": {
                "87:6": {
                    "id": 6
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>We will have you recite, the Qur'n, so that you will not forget, what you recite,</p>"
        },
        "7": {
            "verses": {
                "87:7": {
                    "id": 7
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>except what God may will, that you forget, by abrogating its recitation and its ruling — the Prophet (s) used to recite aloud while Gabriel recited, fearing to forget, and so it is as though it was said to him, `Do not hasten in it; you will not forget and so do not weary yourself by reciting it aloud'; assuredly He, exalted be He, knows what is overt, of words and deeds, and what is hidden, of both of these.</p>"
        },
        "8": {
            "verses": {
                "87:8": {
                    "id": 8
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>And We will ease your way to the easy way, the uncomplicated Law, namely, Islam.</p>"
        },
        "9": {
            "verses": {
                "87:9": {
                    "id": 9
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>So remind, admonish by the Qur'n, in case the reminder should be of benefit, to the one whom you might remind, the one mentioned in [the following verse] `he [who fears] will be reminded', in other words, even if it might not be of benefit, for it is of benefit to some but of no benefit to others.</p>"
        },
        "10": {
            "verses": {
                "87:10": {
                    "id": 10
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>He who fears, God, exalted be He, will be reminded, by it, as in the verse: So admonish by the Qur'n him who fears My threat [Q. 50:45];</p>"
        },
        "11": {
            "verses": {
                "87:11": {
                    "id": 11
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>but the wretched one (al-ashq means al-shaq), that is to say, the disbeliever, will shun it, that is, the reminder, in other words, he will leave it aside, not looking at it,</p>"
        },
        "12": {
            "verses": {
                "87:12": {
                    "id": 12
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>he who will be roasted in the greater Fire, the Fire of the Hereafter, the lesser fire being that of this world;</p>"
        },
        "13": {
            "verses": {
                "87:13": {
                    "id": 13
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>then he will neither die therein, and find rest, nor live, a enjoyable life.</p>"
        },
        "14": {
            "verses": {
                "87:14": {
                    "id": 14
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>Successful, winner, indeed is he who purifies himself, [who] cleanses himself by means of [his adherence to] faith,</p>"
        },
        "15": {
            "verses": {
                "87:15": {
                    "id": 15
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and mentions the Name of his Lord, saying Allhu akbar, `God is Great', and prays, the five prayers — and such are the concerns of [one working towards] the Hereafter, [concerns] which the Meccan disbelievers shun.</p>"
        },
        "16": {
            "verses": {
                "87:16": {
                    "id": 16
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>Nay, but you prefer (or read yu'thirna, `they prefer') the life of this world, to the Hereafter,</p>"
        },
        "17": {
            "verses": {
                "87:17": {
                    "id": 17
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>whereas the Hereafter, and the Paradise it entails, is better and more lasting.</p>"
        },
        "18": {
            "verses": {
                "87:18": {
                    "id": 18
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>Truly this, the success of those who purify themselves, and the Hereafter being better, is in the former scrolls, the ones revealed before the Qur'n,</p>"
        },
        "19": {
            "verses": {
                "87:19": {
                    "id": 19
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>the scrolls of Abraham and Moses, the ten scrolls of Abraham and the Torah of Moses. Meccan, consisting of 26 verses.</p>"
        }
    }
}